1.3.0 2026-05-16
  - DEWS Multi-subject Analysis — Negative Control (epileptic seizures)
    dews_multi.py extends DEWS to sub-047 (7 runs, N=57 ia_nm seizures) and
    sub-035 (14 runs, N=54 a_m_hyperkinetic seizures). NaN guard added to
    skip seizures whose onset falls inside the rolling-variance warm-up period.
    Statistical test: Wilcoxon signed-rank (H0: median ratio = 1.0).
    sub-035: median ratio 1.039, W=597, p=0.21 — clean null confirmed.
    sub-047: median ratio 1.026, W=578, p=0.048 — marginal; driven by runs
    01-02 (early-session seizures, unstable rolling baseline); runs 03/04/07
    show flat/DOWN pattern (ratios 0.89–0.95).
    Overall: no consistent pre-ictal HEP variance rise across N=111 seizures.
    Consistent with HRIT v3 negative control prediction.

1.2.0 2026-05-15
  - DEWS Analysis — Negative Control (epileptic seizures)
    dews_analysis.py computes HEP amplitude and rolling variance for sub-001
    (N=4 focal epileptic seizures). HRIT v3 predicts no systematic pre-ictal
    variance rise in epilepsy (negative control arm). Results: impaired-awareness
    seizures show pre-ictal variance decrease (ratios 0.62, 0.86); aware seizures
    show near-flat variance (1.09, 1.06). Consistent with framework predictions.
    N=1, exploratory only.

